<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="408" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1054,1655]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1054,1079]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Occipital carina distinctly curved above base of mandible, often nearly rectangularly angled with hypostomal carina and connected to hypostomal carina distinctly above base of mandible, resulting a distinct occipital flange; median lamella of frons distinct and normally acute posteriorly; propleuron convex; mesopleuron in front of prepectal carina steep, subvertical (
<figureCitation box="[666,734,1162,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helcon sulcatus sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesosoma, lateral aspect; D, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; E, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827534/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C); prepectal carina present medio-ventrally; first discal cell of fore wing rather wide (
<figureCitation box="[413,482,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helcon sulcatus sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesosoma, lateral aspect; D, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; E, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827534/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A); hind femur comparatively slender and hardly or not serrate (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1285,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acarohelcon varicolor gen. nov. et sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, habitus, lateral aspect; F, head, lateral aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 3</figureCitation>
E, 4D); basal part of first metasomal sternite longer than wide and basally sculptured, well separated from tergite; second metasomal suture between first and second tergites narrow and shallow; fourth–sixth metasomal tergites well exposed behind third tergite.
</paragraph>
